<p>
The network saw a plethora of currencies go through it, including all the major fiat and digital ones. The total XRP volume was <b>456,718,135,629.3340</b>. Large anamoulous transactions resulted in spikes in the USD and CNY currencies in July and February respectively. Consistent payments in AUD, JPY, BTC, ETH, and XLM were present on the network throughout the year.
</p>

<p>
Offers on the other hand were dominated by the <b>XRP/CNY</b> and <b>CNY/XRP</b> pairs, whose volumes (<b>94,382,927</b> and <b>86,523,240</b>) dwarfed the next largest <b>XRP/USD</b> (<b>8,156,685</b>) and <b>USD/XRP</b> (<b>2,874,124</b>) by several orders of magnitude. Crypto/crypto and fiat/crypto pairings seemed to dominate the order books to a larger degree than fiat/fiat.
</p>

